"{\"uid\": \"canadafreepress.com-article-suspect-shoots-at-israeli-consulate-in-munich-on-olympic-massacre-anniversary\", \"text\": \"News on the NetJerusalem Post & Open Source Intel--Bio and Archives--September 5, 2024  News in Brief-News Headlines|CFP Comments|Reader Friendly|Subscribe|Email Us  A man was shot by Munich Police in an area near the Israeli consulate, according to statements by law enforcement.  The Munich police said that officers were operating at the Munich Documentation Center for the History of National Socialism in the Karolinenlatz area, next to the consulate, when officers opened fire on a \\\"suspicious person.\\\" --More...  BREAKING ????????Reports of Intense gunfire outside the Israeli Consulate in Munich, Germany.pic.twitter.com/OwXwmlXuX5  View Comments  News from around the world  Support Canada Free Press  Link, Bookmark, Share, Subscribe, Donate  Support Canada Free Press  Pursuant to Title 17 U.S.C. 107, other copyrighted work is provided for educational purposes, research, critical comment, or debate without profit or payment. If you wish to use copyrighted material from this site for your own purposes beyond the 'fair use' exception, you must obtain permission from the copyright owner. Views are those of authors and not necessarily those of Canada Free Press.  Content is Copyright 1997-2025--the individual authors | Site Copyright 1997-2025 Canada Free Press |Privacy Statement\"}"